tspan.tspan: SIGNAL
GENERATION
While active, the number of Incoming
packets should be greater than 0,
Indicating the
signal flow from BITE or
SPFRx Devices.
Data flow will be true while
there are
visiblity packets coming through.
When scanning, the Rx (recive) sample rate
should match the MT (metatransport)
sample rate. The dish ID should update to
match the expected dish (eg SKA100).
When using BITE, ensure that the BITE
configs are set before running. After
starting LSTV playback, the memory
location will change, showing that the
playback is running through generated
data.
If using SPFRx, the packets comming out of
the device should be increasing, showing
data generation is working.
Prior to scanning, the VCC should be ON,
the scan ID set and equal to the other
SCAN IDs, and the CONFIG ID should
match the intended set up. (Number of
FSPs, etc.)
Prior to scanning, the RDT Should be ON.
When a scan starts, the First input TS
should be set, showing that the data is
flowing through it.
Prior to scanning, the values in the corner
turner should be greater than 0, indicating
that the first timestamp from the corner
turner has been set.
While scanning, the number of outbound
(Tx) packets should change, indicating
data
is being passed out of the Talon
board.
The graph should also show packets of
both signal Tx and Rx increasing, showing a
flow through the system.
Before scanning, the SDP should be on, the
execution block ID should be set, and the
scan ID should match the one set in the
VCC. Monitor the signal display for
monitoring during the scan to esnure data
outflow.
